<h1>Shu Kong (Aimery) </h1>
<!--<p style="font-size:14px"><em>(Aimery is my unofficial name. If you want to know how to pronounce my official name, please click <a href="https://translate.google.com/#auto/en/%E5%AD%94%E5%BA%B6">here</a>.)</em></p>
-->

<p>I am a computer science PhD <del>student</del> candidate at <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu">Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences</a>, <a href="http://www.uci.edu">UC Irvine</a>. I work at the <a href="http://vision.ics.uci.edu">Computational Vision Group</a> where I am advised by <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~fowlkes/">Prof. Charless Fowlkes</a> and working closely with Prof. <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~dramanan/">Deva Ramanan</a>. I am also collaborating with Prof. <a href="http://cinquin.org.uk/?page_id=108">Olivier Cinquin</a> and Prof. <a href="http://www.life.illinois.edu/plantbio/People/Faculty/Punyasena.htm">Surangi Punyasena</a>. 
I am broadly interested in computer vision, machine learning and their applications.
Currently, I'm working on some theory and applications of deep convolutional neural networks, e.g. image aesthetics, bioimage computing, fine-grained classification, keypoint detection, semantic segmentation, object detection, instance segmentation, etc.
An overview of my research can be found in the one-page <a href="./material/ShuKong_research_statement_v1.0.pdf">research statement</a>.
</p>

